threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit LSB executable, Intel 80386, version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Felix Bilstein - yara-signator at cocacoding dot com

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a Linux DDoS bot, likely a variant of the Mirai or Gafgyt families. It contains a comprehensive suite of attack vectors including UDP floods (sub_8049a00, sub_8049770), TCP floods (SYN, ACK, PSH-ACK) (sub_8049fd0, sub_8055f10, sub_8055c00), ICMP floods (sub_80559c0), and SSDP discovery (strings). The binary features a process killer routine (sub_80567a0) that scans /proc to terminate competing malware and utilizes XOR-based string decryption (sub_8057290). It establishes a C2 connection to the IP 94.156.152.6 (sub_8058100) and crafts custom network packets using raw sockets.
